# .env.local — Do Not Overwrite

The PM's local credentials live in `.env.local`. **Never delete, truncate, or overwrite this file** unless the user explicitly asks to restore or sync env vars from Vercel.

## FORBIDDEN (unless user explicitly requests env restore)

- `vercel link` — overwrites `.env.local` with Vercel CLI boilerplate
- `vercel env pull .env.local` — replaces the entire file (drops keys not on Vercel)
- Writing, deleting, or emptying `.env.local` via any tool or shell redirect

## Safe alternatives

- **Deploy preview:** `vercel deploy` (project is already linked via `.vercel/project.json` — do not re-run `vercel link`)
- **Restore env (only when user asks):** back up first, then pull:
  ```bash
  cp .env.local .env.local.backup 2>/dev/null || true
  vercel env pull .env.local --environment=preview --yes
  ```
  Re-merge any local-only keys from `.env.local.backup` or `.env.local.example`.

## Agent checklist

- [ ] Do not read or paste `.env.local` contents in chat
- [ ] Do not run Vercel CLI commands that touch `.env.local` without user approval
- [ ] If deploy fails due to missing link, use existing `.vercel/project.json` or ask the user — do not auto-run `vercel link`
